The paper proposes a framework for discovering a policy basis in reinforcement learning, which involves techniques such as option discovery and skill acquisition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
